                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On October 17, President Truman delivered a nationwide radio address at 11:30 p.
                    m. (<gloss target="#t_EST1">EST</gloss>) from San Francisco. He reported on his
                    meeting with General MacArthur at Wake Island, reiterated the desire of the
                    United States for a unified, independent government for Korea, and stated that
                    the United States had no aggressive design in Korea or any other place in the
                    Far East. (<hi rend="italic">Public Papers of the Presidents of the United
                        States: Harry S. Truman, 1950</hi>, page 673.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
